    <div class="card mt-3">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="card-title">Technologies Used:</h4>
            <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-body-secondary">
                <ul class="fs-5">
                    <li><strong>express: </strong>As the web application framework.</li>
                    <li><strong>mongoose: </strong>For MongoDB object modeling.</li>
                    <li><strong>ejs: </strong>For templating and rendering dynamic HTML.</li>
                    <li><strong>express-ejs-layouts: </strong>To manage layouts in EJS.</li>
                    <li><strong>express-session: </strong>For handling user sessions.</li>
                    <li><strong>connect-flash: </strong>For flash messages to enhance user experience.</li>
                    <li><strong>method-override: </strong>To support PUT and DELETE methods in forms.</li>
                    <li><strong>dotenv: </strong>To manage environment variables securely.</li>
                </ul>
            </h6>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mt-3">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="card-title">Features:</h4>
            <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-body-secondary">
                <ul class="fs-5">
                    <li><strong>Add Customer: </strong>Easily add new customers with their name, email, phone number,
                        and an overview.</li>
                    <li><strong>View Customers: </strong>Display a list of all customers with their details.</li>
                    <li><strong>Update Customer: </strong>Edit existing customer information.</li>
                    <li><strong>Delete Customer: </strong>Remove customers from the system.</li>
                    <li><strong>CRUD Operations: </strong>Full support for Create, Read, Update, and Delete operations.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>MVC Framework: </strong>Structured using the Model-View-Controller pattern for
                        maintainability and scalability.</li>
                    <li><strong>Error Handling: </strong>Robust handling of both asynchronous and synchronous errors to
                        ensure smooth operation and better user experience.</li>
                </ul>
            </h6>
        </div>
    </div>

